text: The Tianhe (), code name "TH", or "Tianhe Core Module" (TCM) is the foundation element of the Tiangong space station. It was launched into orbit on 29 April 2021 as the final stage of Project 921 Tiangong program, part of the Chinese space program. In October 2020, China selected 18 new astronauts ahead of the construction of the space station. ==References== Category:April 2021 events Category:Chinese spacecraft Category:2020s in spaceflight
